I need to get 4k hp, 1200 ac and a bunch of aa points (nd3 and aoe taunt required)... so while I'm working on the aa points I'm not getting drops, I'm not in a guild at the moment and the quality of drops I can get in pick-up groups is pretty poor anyhow.<br>
However, I've been making about 10-20k a week in the bazaar so I'm looking for droppable and often sold upgrades to help me reach the targets... any suggestions?<br>
<br>
Thanks in anticipation <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
(click name links to current magelo profile)<br>
 <p><p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48193">Diddums</a>
Ogre Warlord
7th Hammer
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udinadassshnameless.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DinadassSHnameless</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/02 10:28:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4040.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Upgrade question: need 4k and 1200</span><hr size=1> Replace the cobolt with Champions should get u close to 4k, and can easily buy the MQ's. Then piece together what u need after that. <p><img src="http://www.rit.edu/~rmm5333/newsig4.jpg" ><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140759>Barbie Tanks Gear</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umakiodarkfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makio Darkfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/02 11:22:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4040.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   upgrades</span><hr size=1> add a polished mithril torque or shrouded medallion, and ancient seahorse hide cloak .. those should easily get you to 1200ac<br>
<br>
Makio Darkfury<br>
57th Dwarf Myrmidon<br>
Crusaders of Drunken Might, Fennin Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmallbob60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smallbob60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/02 12:01:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4040.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: upgrades</span><hr size=1> Where did you get that stone with the sweet resists from?<br>
<br>
As for upgrades, if you really are making that much money, look into SS guants MQ.  They add +90 hps, which is nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraunstoncutter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/02 1:41:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4040.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: upgrades</span><hr size=1> Save your CP's again, and get yourself a heavy rubicite girlde for your belt slot.<br>
<br>
Skyshrine quest bracr, arms, helm, and legs should do wonders.  And if you guild can do it, Vindi BP, if not, SS then.<br>
<br>
and ND will do so much for your HPs. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a> <a href="http://www.swordoffate.com"><Sword of Fate></a>

<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124485">Deterious </a> <a href="http://www.swordoffate.com"><Sword of Fate></a>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 736<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/02 2:20:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4040.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Upgrade question: need 4k and 1200</span><hr size=1> Don't waste a dime upgrading your armor!!!<br>
<br>
You are really close to making the minimum requirements so you might as well only get items that won't be getting replaced soon. Presumably, if the guild you are joining has these standards, chances are that their warriors are all better equiped than you, which by default means that you will end up getting a lot of &quot;crap&quot; loot that is a nice upgrade for you but not for them.<br>
<br>
Once you get ND3 you will have darn near 4khp so you don't need to work too hard on that. Maybe get a heavy rubicite girdle since it won't likely be upgraded any time soon anyway. That will also give you 5ac more than the belt you have now.<br>
<br>
You might consider wearing IGS or a Mith torque to get your AC over 1200.<br>
<br>
One other item you might consider is a Horn of Hsagra. It will fix your AC problem and add some HP. Since chances are you won't be MT for a while it wouldn't hurt to weild it, and its really nice DPS anyway. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=353608" target="_blank"><b>Wandorfu</b></a><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udiddums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diddums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/29/02 3:13:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4040.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   thanks</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the advice, I think nd3 is probably my highest priority if it will really make that much difference (10%? so 360hp I guess... that'll get me very close) followed closely by an AC upgrade without sacrificing too many hp.<br>
As an ogre I can't wear IGS (and I wouldn't want to lose the 145hp I get off my chok pauldrons either).  I'm also reluctant to wear my shrouded medallion except for resists, because that means giving up the 66hp from the clattering bone necklace.  Oh, and seahorse cloak would lose me the Cloak of Flames so that's out.<br>
The heavy rubicite girdle is great, last time I saw one for sale he was asking 120k for it (seventh hammer has a seriously messed up economy) which means it's a few weeks saving away, or I can try to exp in CT but it's very tough to find pick-up groups there.<br>
The horn of hsagra is very tempting, it's got a nice ratio too so I wouldn't mind using one for general raiding - not sure how flexible the guild will be about using ac on a weapon to meet their minimums, but they will probably be cool if I intend to use it most of the time I'd guess <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
The SS gaunts look very good, (I've been mooching through the armor comparision chart from the faq at the top of this thread) so I think I'll try to replace a few pieces of my cobalt with SS armor (myrm is out cos I'm on CoV ally faction and so is the guild I wish to join) to get my AC bumped up a bit too.<br>
<br>
Thanks again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
